g.text: A data set collection of positive/negative bug samples:
- Bug Samples from both positive and negative bug samples are combined to training and
evaluation sequences. Please note that the bug samples are still contained by their data
A sample of a bug corresponds to a model version:
- Computes initially the node self embeddings for all nodes in all location subgraphs from the
current model version.- Bug location samples are relocated to their containers if needed,
e.g., Operations to Classes if the current training targets classifiers only.
A sample of bug location corresponds to a model element:
- Positive samples correspond to the model elements in the buggy model version that were
modified to produce the fixed version (corresponds to the bug fix commit in the repository)
- Negative samples are randomly selected from the model version. The number of samples
per type can be configured. Library model element, e.g., Java String, Integer, are filtered
A potential bug location corresponds to a model element:
- Positive samples correspond to the model elements in the buggy model version that were
modified to produce the fixed version (corresponds to the bug fix commit in the repository)
- All model element in a specific version are potential bug locations. The type of samples, e.g.,
class or operation, can be configured. Library model element, e.g., Java String, Integer, are
filtered from the potential location sampels.
A data set collection of model version and bug reports:
- Computes initially the node self embeddings for all nodes in the test data set.
- Library nodes, e.g., Java String, Integer, are filtered as potential bug locations.
A bug report and the model version for prediction:
- Contains a location sample for each model element in the corresponding version.
